<p></p>
<p>The Recaman&rsquo;s sequence is de&#64257;ned by a0 = 0 ; for m &gt; 0, a(m) = a(m&minus;1) &minus; m if the resulting a(m) is positive and not already in the sequence, otherwise a(m) = a(m&minus;1) + m. The &#64257;rst few numbers in the Recaman&rsquo;s Sequence is 0, 1, 3,6, 2, 7, 13, 20, 12, 21, 11, 22, 10, 23, 9 &middot; &middot; &middot; .</p>
<p>Given k, your task is to calculate ak.</p>
<h3 style="text-align: center;">Input</h3>
<p>The input consists of several test cases. Each line of the input contains an integer k where 0 &le; k &le; 500000. The last line contains an integer &minus;1, which should not be processed.</p>
<pre><br />Sample Input<br />7<br />10000<br />-1<br /></pre>
<h3 style="text-align: center;">Output</h3>
<pre> <br />For each k given in the input, print one line containing ak to the output.<br /><br />Sample output<br />20<br />18658<br /></pre>
<p> </p>

